value.value: This gene is involved in the immune responsiveness of B-cells.

Human CD24 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6q21 and is approximately 2 kb in length. This allele, which encodes signal transducer CD24 protein, is involved in B-cell functional modulation. Elevated expression levels of the wild type allele may indicate early stage cancer.
Signal transducer CD24 (80 aa, ~8 kDa) is encoded by the human CD24 gene. This protein mediates B-cell function and may play a role in tumor cell metastasis.
This gene may play a role in cell growth and the cell cycle.

Human APOBEC3G wild-type allele is located within 22q13.1-q13.2 and is approximately 47 kb in length. This allele, which encodes DNA dC->dU-editing enzyme APOBEC-3G protein, may be involved in cellular growth regulation, cell cycle modulation and viral infectivity inhibition.
A cutaneous lymphoma which contains more than 15 centroblasts per 40X high-power microscopic field.
A chromosome band present on 22q

label.value: DNA dC to dU-Editing Enzyme APOBEC-3G

value.value: DNA dC->dU-editing enzyme APOBEC-3G protein (384 aa, ~46 kDa) is encoded by the human APOBEC3G gene. This protein is a member of the cytidine deaminase gene family and may play a role in editing mRNA, cellular growth and cell cycle control. The enzyme inhibits the viral replication of several virion species; however, the lethality of human T-cell leukemia virus type I may exhibit resistance to the activity of this enzyme.
This gene is involved in mitosis and meiosis.

Human AURKB wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17p13.1 and is approximately 6 kb in length. This allele, which encodes serine/threonine-protein kinase 12, plays a role in chromosome segregation modulation during cellular mitosis and meiosis.
The period of time between two dates or events or between the beginning and end of something.
Unsolicited report received by surveillance system via either the voluntary or mandatory route.

Aurora kinase B (344 aa, ~39 kDa) is encoded by the human AURKB gene. This protein plays a role in both the modulation of microtubule structure and facilitation of chromosome segregation during mitosis and meiosis.
A report that is mandated by law and/or regulation.
Involving only one part or side.

Peptides with direct synaptic effects or indirect modulatory effects on the nervous system. A neuropeptide is a molecule released by neurons as an intercellular neurotransmitter. Alternatively, neuropeptides can be released by non-neuronal cells as hormones. They are endogenous peptides such as endorphins that influence neural activity or functioning.

label.value: Primary Cutaneous Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma

value.value: An anaplastic large cell lymphoma limited to the skin at the time of diagnosis.  Most patients present with solitary or localized skin lesions, which may be tumors, nodules or papules.  The t(2;5) translocation that is present in many cases of systemic anaplastic large cell lymphoma, is not found in this disease. (WHO, 2001)
This gene plays a role in signal transduction.

Human FLOT2 wild-type allele is located within 17q11-q12 and is approximately 18 kb in length. This allele, which encodes flotillin 2 protein, is involved in the maintenance of caveolae structure, cellular adhesion and neuronal signaling. The determination of the level of the expression of the wild-type allele may be utilized to characterize early carcinogenesis.
Flotillin-2 (379 aa, ~42 kDa) is encoded by the human FLOT2 gene. This protein plays a role in neuronal signaling and caveolar membrane structure.
Concise expression about the atoms that constitute a particular chemical compound.

label.value: Hospitalization or Prolongation of Existing Hospitalization Required

value.value: An indication or description that an extended period of hospitalization is necessary.

label.value: Persistent or Significant Disability or Incapacity

value.value: An indication or description of a continuing and significant impairment.

A consortium of professional organizations dedicated to improving survival and quality of life for cancer patients through standard-setting, prevention, research, education, and the monitoring of comprehensive quality care.
A person or agency that promotes or exchanges goods or services for money; a seller.
A therapeutically active agent, treatment regimen or procedure that is intended to provide baseline measurements for the experimental protocol of a clinical trial.

label.value: Choroid Spindle Cell Type A Melanoma

value.value: A choroid melanoma characterized by the presence of malignant spindle-shaped melanocytes with slender nuclei and no visible nucleoli.

A non-keratinizing carcinoma arising from the oropharynx.  It is characterized by the presence of large malignant cells with vesicular nuclei, prominent nucleoli, syncytial growth pattern, and a lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate.

A rare, keratinizing or non-keratinizing squamous cell carcinoma arising from the mucosal epithelium of the nasal cavity or the paranasal sinuses.  It affects most often the maxillary sinus.  Less frequently, it arises from the nasal cavity, ethmoid sinus, sphenoid sinus, and frontal sinus.  Symptoms include nasal fullness, epistaxis, rhinorhea, pain, and paresthesia.  Patients with nasal squamous cell carcinoma usually present earlier than patients with maxillary sinus carcinoma and have a better prognosis compared to the latter group.
A therapeutically active agent that is intended to provide baseline measurements for the experimental protocol of a clinical trial.
An adverse event that occurred after the patient had completed a clinical study (including any protocol-required post-treatment follow-up).
Property used to indicate that an amino acid is essential and must be included in the diet.
The calendar date on which a person was born.
The calendar date on which something is to start or did start.
The calendar date on which something is to terminate or did terminate.

label.value: Adverse Event Conditionally Related to Intervention

value.value: A characteristic used to qualify the adverse event as unclassified in term of its relation to the medical intervention. According to WHO causality assessment criteria of suspected adverse reactions it is applicable to clinical event, including laboratory test abnormality, reported as an adverse reaction, about which more data is essential for a proper assessment or the additional data are under examination.

label.value: Adverse Event Relation to Intervention Unclassifiable

value.value: A characteristic used to qualify the adverse event as unclassifiable in term of its relation to the medical intervention. According to WHO causality assessment criteria of suspected adverse reactions it is applicable to an adverse reaction which cannot be judged because information about it is insufficient or contradictory, and cannot be supplemented or verified.

label.value: Choroid Spindle Cell Type B Melanoma

value.value: A choroid melanoma characterized by the presence of malignant spindle-shaped melanocytes with larger nuclei and distinct nucleoli.
The withdrawal of a medical intervention.
Reintroduction of previously withdrawn medical intervention in the same patient.
A report or observation of one or more adverse events that must be submitted within a specified amount of time due to the severity of one or more of the events.
Action(s) undertaken to indicate that a previously transmitted report should be considered completely void (nullified).
A mature or immature teratoma occurring in children.
A childhood benign or malignant germ cell tumor arising from an anatomic site other than the brain.

label.value: Childhood Malignant Testicular Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: A malignant germ cell tumor in children arising from the testis.  It includes the embryonal carcinoma, yolk sac tumor, choriocarcinoma, and mixed germ cell tumors.

label.value: Childhood Malignant Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: A malignant germ cell tumor in children arising from the ovary.  It includes the dysgerminoma, yolk sac tumor, choriocarcinoma, embryonal carcinoma and immature teratoma.
